    "title": {
      "rendered": "12 Google+ Best Practices for Nonprofits"
    },
    "content": {
      "rendered": "<p><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/12-Google%2B-Page-Best-Practices-for-Nonprofits.jpg\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-16384 alignright\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"12 Google+ Page Best Practices for Nonprofits\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/12-Google%2B-Page-Best-Practices-for-Nonprofits-300x300.jpg?resize=300%2C300\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/12-Google%2B-Page-Best-Practices-for-Nonprofits.jpg?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/12-Google%2B-Page-Best-Practices-for-Nonprofits.jpg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/12-Google%2B-Page-Best-Practices-for-Nonprofits.jpg?resize=200%2C200&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/12-Google%2B-Page-Best-Practices-for-Nonprofits.jpg?resize=75%2C75&amp;ssl=1 75w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/12-Google%2B-Page-Best-Practices-for-Nonprofits.jpg?w=500&amp;ssl=1 500w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a><strong><a href=\"https://plus.google.com/+nonprofitorgs/posts\">Google+ Pages</a></strong> have a vast tool set and Google&#8217;s quest to integrate Google+ into their most popular products, such as Search, Gmail, YouTube, Local, and Wallet, is paying off as <strong><a href=\"http://www.pinterest.com/pin/203154633166200962/\">active monthly users continue to grow</a></strong>. That said, Google+ is low on the priority lists of most nonprofits. Many nonprofits are curious, but lack the resources necessary to create and manage yet another social network.</p>\n<p>Google+ isn&#8217;t for all nonprofits, but for those that have actively adopted a pro-social media policy, it&#8217;s worth the time investment to experiment with Google+. In the process, your nonprofit at the very least will increase your<strong><a href=\"http://www.nptechforgood.com/2013/04/29/google-search-results-now-prominently-feature-nonprofit-google-pages/\"> SEO in Google Search</a></strong>\u00a0and position yourself as an early adopter of <strong><a href=\"http://www.nten.org/articles/2014/mobile-for-good-how-mobile-wallets-will-transform-fundraising\">digital wallets</a></strong>. For those nonprofits already active on Google+ or for those willing to take the leap, below are 12 Google+ Page best practices to help get you started.</p>\n<hr />\n<h2>1. Prioritize uploading photos over sharing links.</h2>\n<p>Google+ is a visual social network. Posts with with a message and an uploaded image get much higher engagement than shared links.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://plus.google.com/103858765220369650172/posts/F8gmSNh6Pfo\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-16347\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"Jane Goodall Google+\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Jane-Goodall-Google%2B.png?resize=600%2C565\" width=\"600\" height=\"565\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Jane-Goodall-Google%2B.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Jane-Goodall-Google%2B.png?resize=300%2C282&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p>1. Write your post and include a link.<br />\n2. Delete the generated thumbnail and link that appears.<br />\n3. Upload a larger version the photo and then share.</p>\n<h2>2. Experiment with animated .GIFs.</h2>\n<p>What&#8217;s old is new again. Animated .GIFs are making a comeback. You can upload them as posts or as cover photos on Google+ Pages. See the <strong><a href=\"https://plus.google.com/+sierraclub/posts\">Sierra Club&#8217;s Google+ Page</a></strong>\u00a0to view an example of an animated .GIF being used as a cover photo.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://plus.google.com/+sierraclub/posts\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-16349\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"Sierra Club an Google+\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Sierra-Club-an-Google%2B.png?resize=600%2C271\" width=\"600\" height=\"271\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Sierra-Club-an-Google%2B.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Sierra-Club-an-Google%2B.png?resize=300%2C135&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2>3. Curate good content through sharing.</h2>\n<p>Most nonprofits do not create enough of their own content to be active daily on Google+. By sharing other&#8217;s content, you can effectively engage and inspire your followers.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://plus.google.com/+GLBLCTZN/posts/8VgwHoXHzkk\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-16352\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"Global Citizen an Google+ 3\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Global-Citizen-an-Google%2B-3.png?resize=600%2C318\" width=\"600\" height=\"318\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Global-Citizen-an-Google%2B-3.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Global-Citizen-an-Google%2B-3.png?resize=300%2C159&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://plus.google.com/+GLBLCTZN/posts/8VgwHoXHzkk\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-16353\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"Global Citizen an Google+ 2\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Global-Citizen-an-Google%2B-2.png?resize=600%2C454\" width=\"600\" height=\"454\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Global-Citizen-an-Google%2B-2.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Global-Citizen-an-Google%2B-2.png?resize=300%2C227&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2>\u00a04. Tag other pages in your poststo foster good will.</h2>\n<p>By adding a &#8220;+&#8221; symbol in front of page names, your nonprofit can foster good will with funders, partners, and supporters.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://plus.google.com/+nonprofitorgs/posts\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-16354\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"Public Interest Registry on Google+\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Public-Interest-Registry-on-Google%2B.png?resize=600%2C302\" width=\"600\" height=\"302\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Public-Interest-Registry-on-Google%2B.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Public-Interest-Registry-on-Google%2B.png?resize=300%2C151&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2>5. +1 the content posted by others to increase the exposure of your nonprofit&#8217;s avatar.</h2>\n<p>Regularly &#8220;+1&#8221; the content of other to increase exposure of your nonprofit&#8217;s Google+ Page and thus grow your followers.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://plus.google.com/b/103858765220369650172/+WWF/posts\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-16356\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"WWF on Google+\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/WWF-on-Google%2B.png?resize=600%2C475\" width=\"600\" height=\"475\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/WWF-on-Google%2B.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/WWF-on-Google%2B.png?resize=300%2C237&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2>6. Merge your YouTube Channel with your nonprofit&#8217;s Google+ Page.</h2>\n<p>Google is committed to weaving Google+ through out their suite of products and <strong><a href=\"http://www.nptechforgood.com/2013/05/05/how-to-merge-your-nonprofits-youtube-channel-and-google-page/\">merging your nonprofit&#8217;s YouTube Channel with your Google+ Page</a></strong> can help increase both your Google Search SEO and your TouTube SEO.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://plus.google.com/+amnestyusa/posts\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-16364\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"Amnesty International Google+\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Amnesty-International-Google%2B1.png?resize=600%2C415\" width=\"600\" height=\"415\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Amnesty-International-Google%2B1.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Amnesty-International-Google%2B1.png?resize=300%2C207&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2>7. Have more than one manager for your Google+ Page.</h2>\n<p>In your Dashboard under &#8220;Settings&#8221; add at least two managers to ensure that your nonprofit does not lose access to your Google+ Page due to staff and volunteer turnover.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Google%2B-Managers1.png\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-16365\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"Google+ Managers\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Google%2B-Managers1.png?resize=600%2C327\" width=\"600\" height=\"327\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Google%2B-Managers1.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Google%2B-Managers1.png?resize=300%2C163&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2>8. Reserve your Google+ Page URL.</h2>\n<p>In your Dashboard under &#8220;About&#8221; reserve a Google+ Page URL for your nonprofit. Ideally your URLs are consistent across all of your nonprofit&#8217;s social networks.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Google%2B-URL.png\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-16363\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"Google+ URL\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Google%2B-URL.png?resize=600%2C307\" width=\"600\" height=\"307\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Google%2B-URL.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Google%2B-URL.png?resize=300%2C153&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2>9. Regularly monitor your Google+ Page Insights.</h2>\n<p>Google+ Insights will help your nonprofit get a clear understanding of what kind of content your followers engage with most as well as their demographics.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Insights-1.png\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-16366\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"Insights 1\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Insights-1.png?resize=600%2C302\" width=\"600\" height=\"302\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Insights-1.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Insights-1.png?resize=300%2C151&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Insights-2.png\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-16367\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"Insights 2\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Insights-2.png?resize=600%2C236\" width=\"600\" height=\"236\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Insights-2.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Insights-2.png?resize=300%2C118&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Insights-3.png\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-16368\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"Insights 3\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Insights-3.png?resize=600%2C268\" width=\"600\" height=\"268\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Insights-3.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Insights-3.png?resize=300%2C134&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2>10. Create &#8220;Events&#8221; for Google+ Hangouts on Air.</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"http://www.google.com/+/learnmore/events/\">Google+ Events</a></strong> allow followers to RSVP to your Hangout on Air and enable real-time conversations while the Hangout on Air is occurring. Events also serve as a chronological history of your nonprofit&#8217;s Google+ Hangouts on Air.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Google%2B-Events-1.png\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-16373\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"Google+ Events 1\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Google%2B-Events-1.png?resize=600%2C298\" width=\"600\" height=\"298\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Google%2B-Events-1.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Google%2B-Events-1.png?resize=300%2C149&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Google%2B-Events-2.png\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-16374\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"Google+ Events 2\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Google%2B-Events-2.png?resize=600%2C520\" width=\"600\" height=\"520\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Google%2B-Events-2.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Google%2B-Events-2.png?resize=300%2C260&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2>11. Claim your Google+ Local Page.</h2>\n<p>Location-based nonprofits already have a presence on Google+ though most do not know it. <strong><a href=\"https://plus.google.com/108601826331581658642/about\">Google+ Local Pages</a></strong> are given priority placement in Google Search results, so be sure to sign up for <a href=\"http://www.google.com/+/learnmore/local/\"><strong>Google+ Local</strong></a> and claim your Google+ Local Page.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://plus.google.com/108601826331581658642/about\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-16376\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"MOMA on Google+\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/MOMA-on-Google%2B1.png?resize=600%2C458\" width=\"600\" height=\"458\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/MOMA-on-Google%2B1.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/MOMA-on-Google%2B1.png?resize=300%2C229&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2><strong>12. Sign up for the Google for Nonprofits Program.</strong></h2>\n<p>When (and let&#8217;s hope it is soon) Google+ adds Google Wallet &#8220;Donate&#8221; buttons to Google+ Pages <strong><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/user/SavetheChildrenUSA\">(like it has to YouTube Channels)</a></strong>, your nonprofit will be one step ahead in utilizing digital wallets for online fundraising. The first step is to sign up for the <strong><a href=\"http://www.google.com/nonprofits/\">Google for Nonprofits Program</a></strong>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.google.com/nonprofits/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-16378\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"Google for Nonprofits\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Google-for-Nonprofits1.png?resize=600%2C318\" width=\"600\" height=\"318\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Google-for-Nonprofits1.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Google-for-Nonprofits1.png?resize=300%2C159&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/user/SavetheChildrenUSA\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-16379\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"nonprofit google donate wallet button\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/nonprofit-google-donate-wallet-button.png?resize=600%2C310\" width=\"600\" height=\"310\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/nonprofit-google-donate-wallet-button.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/nonprofit-google-donate-wallet-button.png?resize=300%2C155&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<hr />\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 17px;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold;\"><em>Mobile for Good: A How-To Fundraising Guide for Nonprofits</em></span></span></strong></h2>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Mobile-Good-How--Fundraising-Nonprofits/dp/0071825460\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-16024\" style=\"margin: 10px; border: 1px solid black;\" alt=\"mobile for good look inside\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/mobile-for-good-look-inside.jpg?resize=99%2C150\" width=\"99\" height=\"150\" /></a>Based on more than 20 years of experience and 25,000+ hours spent utilizing mobile and social media, <a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Mobile-Good-How--Fundraising-Nonprofits/dp/0071825460\"><em><strong>Mobile for Good: A How-To Fundraising Guide for Nonprofits</strong></em></a> is a comprehensive 256-page book packed with more than 500 best practices. Written on the premise that all communications and fundraising are now mobile and social, Mobile for Good is a step-by-step how-to guide for writing, implementing, and maintaining a mobile and social fundraising strategy for your nonprofit.<br />\n<strong> </strong></p>\n",
